lement","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Certain sounds have a quality that makes them singable called pitch.\n  With pitch, we now have the ability to identify whether a noise sounds high or low.\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the earlier centuries, musicians have to find a way to reproduce their recordings.\n  Similar to how words and ideas can be recorded with writing, music has been recorded in paper.\n  The earlier notation uses simpler concept but as time progresses the notation does improve to be the modern musical notation that musicians around the world use today.\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To easily identify the pieces of music, the notes have names.\n  Some identify them with the doremi syllables (e.g., do, re, mi, fa, so, la, ti), some name them after the letters (e.g., A, B, C, D, E, F, G), and some even with "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"wikipedia:Numbered musical notation"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"numbers"}]},{"type":"text","value":".\n"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this course, we're using letter names and it often starts with C similarly to the piano.\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A set of notes called an octave is formed with the names.\n  Despite the name, it is built with 7 note names (e.g., A, B, C, D, E, F, G, and then back to A).\n"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"An octave, despite the number, really has 12 pitch classes.\n  The full 12 pitch classes is easily visualized with a piano.\n  Between each of the 12 pitch classes, the distance is a semitone which intuitively means half-note.\n  When the distance of each note is 2 semitone, it is considered as a tone.\n"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"/assets/fds-visual-octaves-and-tones.png"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"an interval is two pitches with a certain distance\n"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"starting from a note, the number of tones distanced between them is the name of an interval\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"e.g., C and D is a second, C to E is a third, D to G is a fourth, F to C is a fifth\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"scales is a group of notes that give the flavor of the music (e.g., melancholic, gleeful)\n"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"also describes the relationship of each note\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"each scale has a tonic which usually named after the first note\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the common type of scales introduced are the diatonic scales, made up of seven notes with two semitones and five tones in it\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"e.g., the C scale is made up of the notes C, D, E, F, G, A, B, C has a pattern of TTSTTTS (tone = T, semitone = S)\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a major scale has a pattern of TTSTTTS, a minor scale has a pattern of TSTTSTT\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"different tonics = different pattern of semitones and tones = different quality and flavor = different melodies\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"each of tonics in diatonic scale is called a mode (e.g., A is called Aeolian mode, E is Phrygian)\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Aeolian mode is a natural minor mode (has a pattern of TSTTSTT)\n"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ionian mode is a natural major mode (has a pattern of TTSTTTS)\n"}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["src-block"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","proper